Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art on rock surface showing dynastic Egyptian relief engraving showing two-horse chariot, upright and facing right, with top half flaked off. Block behind shows torsos and legs of two human figures, upright, right figure leaning towards left figure which kneels on left knee. Hieroglyphic text at base of these. New Kalabsha, Egypt. Scanned
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
